# Vercel rebuilds the app on its own servers, so generated output, dependencies,
# VCS data, local artifacts and the accidental nested repo copy don't need to be
# uploaded. Trimming them keeps the deployment small and, crucially, stops the
# nested repo's node_modules/.next (~1.7GB) from being swept into serverless
# function traces (which caused "functions exceeded the 250 MB" errors).
#
# IMPORTANT: Vercel's ignore matcher does NOT honor leading-slash anchoring and
# matches case-insensitively, so every rule is UNANCHORED. Dependency/build
# rules stay unanchored on purpose so nested copies (e.g. inside ROVEXO/) are
# excluded too.

.next
node_modules
out
build
coverage
test-results
playwright-report
owner-review-screenshots
.git
.vercel
*.tsbuildinfo
vercel-preview-deploy.log

# Accidental nested repository copy (~47k files, ~1.7GB). Because matching is
# unanchored AND case-insensitive, "ROVEXO" also matches the legitimate
# "styles/rovexo/" folder — so re-include that explicitly, otherwise
# app/layout.tsx's `import "@/styles/rovexo/index.css"` fails to resolve.
ROVEXO
!styles/rovexo
!styles/rovexo/**
